A thoroughly unconvincing Juventus earned the 1-0 win away to Palermo thanks only to a deflected Dani Alves effort, as tactical experiments did not pay off.

The Bianconeri got back on top of the table with the midweek 4-0 demolition of Cagliari, but missed Medhi Benatia and Claudio Marchisio, while resting Giorgio Chiellini and Paulo Dybala
